  eli5: "Imagine you have a coloring book. Normally, only one friend can use it. But what if you could magically copy any page and give it to every friend in the whole school? That is what digital products are! You can make a fun worksheet, a cool planner, or a storybook on the computer, and then sell copies to everyone in the world — and you never run out. Some things are cheap like stickers (printables), some are like a big box of LEGOs (courses), and some are in between (eBooks).",
